# Loopretto - top-level (direct) dependencies only. This is the manifest;
# requirements.txt is the resolved lockfile (with transitive pins).
#
# Regenerate the lockfile after editing this file:
#   uv pip compile requirements.in -o requirements.txt
#
# yt-dlp is a RANGE, not a pin, on purpose: YouTube changes its extractors
# often, so a stale yt-dlp pin silently breaks downloads (§8.3). Keep it a
# range in the lockfile too.
